# Makan, Khaybullinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Makan (; , Maqan) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Makansky Selsoviet, Khaybullinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 1,288 as of 2010. There are 12 streets.
Geography
Makan is located 16&nbsp;km southwest of Akyar (the district's administrative centre) by road. Mambetovo is the nearest rural locality.
